  "prompt": "Why can't I see views on my Instagram videos?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're unable to see views on your Instagram videos. Here are a few potential explanations:\n\n1. **Privacy Settings:** If your account or the video has certain privacy settings, such as being marked private, the views might not be displayed publicly or even to you.\n\n2. **App Version:** You might be using an outdated version of the Instagram app. Make sure you have the latest version installed from your device's app store.\n\n3. **Glitches or Bugs:** Technical issues or bugs in the Instagram app can sometimes prevent views from displaying properly. Restarting the app or your device might help resolve this issue.\n\n4. **Server or Connectivity Issues:** Sometimes, connection issues can cause certain features to not load properly. Ensure you have a stable internet connection.\n\n5. **Account Type:** Business and creator accounts on Instagram typically have access to more detailed analytics and insights, including views. Personal accounts might have limited access to such data.\n\n6. **Video Format or Type:** Reels, IGTV videos, and regular video posts might have different ways of displaying views. Ensure you're checking the correct type of video content.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, you might want to reach out directly to Instagram support for assistance with this issue.",
